               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18430508-name-1457" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18430508-name-1457" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430508-name-1457" type="surname" value="WALKER"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430508-name-1457" type="given" value="PETER"></interp>PETER WALKER</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a shipwright, and live at Blackwall. On the 18th of April I was at Greenwich fair—I saw my handkerchief in the hands of Kemp, the officer—I claimed it in the prisoner's presence—it had been in my possession five minutes before.</p>
               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="184305080188"></xptr>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18430508-name-1458" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18430508-name-1458" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430508-name-1458" type="surname" value="KEMP"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430508-name-1458" type="given" value="GEORGE"></interp>GEORGE KEMP</persName>
                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">police-constable N</hi> 82.) I was on duty in Greenwich fair on the 18th of April—I saw the prisoners in company, attempting several gentlemen's pockets—I saw Mr. Walker and another gentleman walking along arm in arm—the prisoners followed them close, and put their hands into each of the gentlemen's pockets—Cockran took up Mr. Walker's pocket, and Goodman the other—Cockran got a handkerchief out of Mr. Walker's pocket, and put it behind him for his companion to take it—I was behind—I took hold of him and the handkerchief—I found two other handkerchiefs on him—Goodman was quite close to him, and could see what he did.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18430508-name-1459" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18430508-name-1459" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430508-name-1459" type="surname" value="BURCHAM"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430508-name-1459" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>THOMAS BURCHAM</persName>
                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">police-constable H</hi> 33.) I was with Kemp—I saw the prisoners trying several gentlemen's pockets—they then went behind the pro<lb></lb>secutor, Cockran lifted his coat, and took his handkerchief out—Goodman was covering him by walking close behind him—in going to the station Cockram <hi rend="italic">chucked</hi> his cap off behind him, and I found another handkerchief in it—the gentleman who was in company with Mr. Walker did not lose anything</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Goodman.</hi> I know nothing of this lad. I did not not put my hand into any pockets.</p>
